SIMPLE: lair
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lair
<hw>Lair</hw> <pr>(l⟦acir⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>leir</ets>, AS. <ets>leger</ets>; akin to D. <ets>leger</ets>, G.
<ets>lager</ets> couch, lair, OHG. <ets>legar</ets>, Goth.
<ets>ligrs</ets>, and to E. <ets>lie</ets>. See <er>Lie</er> to be
prostrate, and cf. <er>Layer</er>, <er>Leaguer</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A place in which to lie or rest; especially, the bed
or couch of a wild beast.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A burying place.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>
<rj><au>Jamieson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A pasture; sometimes, food.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Laird</ent>⟦br⟧
